revision.text:
'''COASTMAP''' is an [[mnemonic]] [[acronym]] to remember key questions for a person's [[psychiatric history]]<ref>[https://sites.google.com/site/litparamedic2013/student-sites/travis-blount/chapter-28-objectives Paramedic Class. Chapter 28 Objectives]</ref>. The mnemonic are often used in the field of emergency medicine by paramedics during the secondary assessment.
==Meaning== The parts of the mnemonic are:
{| | C | — | '''C'''onsciousness |- | O | — | '''O'''rientation |- | A | — | '''A'''ctivity |- | S | — | '''S'''peech |- | T | — | '''T'''hought |- | M | — | '''M'''emory |- | A | — | '''A'''ffect and mood |- | P | — | '''P'''erception |}
==See also== *[[OPQRST]] *[[SOAP note|SOAP]] *[[SAMPLE history|SAMPLE]]
==References== {{reflist}}
{{Medical records}} {{Medical mnemonics}}
[[Category:Medical mnemonics]] [[Category:Mnemonic acronyms]] [[Category:Psychiatry]]

{{italic title}} {{Infobox artwork | image = Cigarette_tony_smith.jpg | painting_alignment = | image_size = | title = Cigarette | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = [[Tony Smith (sculptor)|Tony Smith]] | year = {{Start date|1961}} <!--remove date template if before 1583 CE --> | height_metric = | width_metric = | length_metric = | height_imperial = <!--Place in inches*, it will auto-convert to cm* (*or whatever is defined for these units below)--> | width_imperial = <!--Place in inches*, it will auto-convert to cm* (*or whatever is defined for these units below)--> | length_imperial = <!--Place in inches*, it will auto-convert to cm* (*or whatever is defined for these units below)--> | diameter__metric = | diameter_imperial = | imperial_unit = in<!--don't leave this parameter blank--> | metric_unit = cm<!--don't leave this parameter blank--> | city = | museum = | coordinates = {{Coord|42.93153|-78.87632|format=dms|display=inline,title|type:landmark_region:US-NY}} | owner = }} '''''Cigarette''''' is a public artwork by [[United States]] artist [[Tony Smith (sculptor)|Tony Smith]], located on the grounds of the [[Albright Knox Art Gallery]] in [[Buffalo, New York|Buffalo]], [[New York (state)|NY]]. '''Cigarette''' is a [[minimalist]] piece of [[environmental sculpture]] created by in 1961. The sculpture is over 15 feet tall and made of flat planes of [[steel]] in a twisted form.<ref>{{cite web|title=Cigarette catalog entry|url=http://www.albrightknox.org/collection/search/piece:1772/|publisher=Albright Knox Art Gallery|accessdate=2 July 2012}}</ref> This is the first in an edition of three (with one [[artists proof]]); no. 2 is at [[MOMA]] in New York.
A small scale version of the piece is on display at the [[St. Louis Art Museum]].
==See also== * [[List of Tony Smith sculptures]] * [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Public art/TheArtistResearchProject/TonySmith|The Tony Smith Artist Research Project in Wikipedia]]
